accomplishment_publications.name: Identifying the advantageous latent space dimensionality for StyleGANs used in industrial machine vision applications
accomplishment_publications.publisher: SPIE, AI and Optical Data Sciences IV
accomplishment_publications.description: This work presents an evaluation framework to assess the capabilities of generative models to learn the features and characteristics of the original data consistently and reliably. Feature consistency is proposed as an evaluation criterium to estimate the performance of the generative models. The quality of generated images is quantitatively evaluated, with a focus on determining how the latent space size affects the outcome. Latent space size systematically varied during training on industrially relevant datasets with representative features. Based on the application-specific and human-interpretable features, the image quality of multiple StyleGANs with varying latent space dimensionalities is compared using statistical tests to select the most favorable latent space dimension.

accomplishment_publications.name: Biomedical Data-to-Text Generation via Fine-Tuning Transformers
accomplishment_publications.description:
Abstract: 
Data-to-text (D2T) generation in the biomedical domain is a promising - yet mostly unexplored - field of research. Here, we apply neural models for D2T generation to a real-world dataset consisting of package leaflets of European medicines. We show that fine-tuned transformers are able to generate realistic, multi-sentence text from data in the biomedical domain, yet have important limitations. We also release a new dataset (BioLeaflets) for benchmarking D2T generation models in the biomedical domain.
